  "prompt": "What is origin of \"Nehru\" surname?",
  "response": "The surname \"Nehru\" has its origins in India. It comes from the word \"nehr\" in Hindustani, which means \"canal\" or \"stream.\" The name was first associated with a person who lived near a canal. The Nehru family is one of the prominent families in Indian history, with several members having played significant roles in the country's independence movement and its post-independence politics. The most famous bearer of the surname is Jawaharlal Nehru, who was the first Prime Minister of independent India.",
